textBeforeTable: 2013 Recruit Class . click here to view all the candidates and vote The votes are already rolling in, so A poster of the All-Century Team will be printed and will be given to 2013 season ticket buyers. The poster, featuring photos of all team members, will also be available for purchase. The final All-Century roster will be determined by the fan vote (which will count 50 percent toward the final decision) and by a selection committee, and the team will be announced on April 13 at the Green-White Spring Football Game at Apogee Stadium. A 25-person selection panel made up of North Texas Athletics Hall of Fame members, football lettermen, sports-information personnel, and members of the media - including Joe Greene, Jordan Case, George Dunham, Bill Mercer, Dave Barnett, Ken Bahnsen, Bill Carrico, Toby Gowin, C. Dan Smith, Patrick Cobbs and Byron Gross - chose the more than 120 players that made the ballot. Fan voting starts February 6 and ends on March 13. The online ballot will go live on meangreensports.com on February 6, and paper ballots will be available at North Texas basketball games, the North Texas Athletic Ticket Office, or by contacting the athletic department. .
